response.Q0:
If the number revealed by the inspector was negative I would go the furthest direction away from that one. 

I mainly clicked the furthest out nodules each time which cost more but I think ultimately served me better. If it was above +15 I knew I'd be in the green going to that destination
response.Q1: I feel like I did get better as I went on, I switched up the nodules I inspected as in I went to different ends of the map and used law of averages to work out that the same one that had +81 before but not the next time
response.Q2: It was tricky at times because when it was a smaller positive number, eg +12 , it's hard to tell if that route would make gains or losses so was more of a lottery
Best of luck with all your research! (That was fun!)
